files.Title: WeihanLi.Common.Helpers.Combinatorics.Combinations<T>
files.Summary: Combinations defines a sequence of all possible subsets of a particular size from the set of values. Within the returned set, there is no prescribed order. This follows the mathematical concept of choose. For example, put 10 dominoes in a hat and pick 5. The number of possible combinations is defined as "10 choose 5", which is calculated as (10!) / ((10 - 5)! * 5!).

files.Title: WeihanLi.Common.Helpers.Combinatorics.Variations<T>
files.Summary: Variations defines a sequence of all possible ordered subsets of a particular size from the set of values.
